CommonFields.Title: Properties and structure of poly(vinyl alcohol)/silica composites
Author: Nakane, Koji
Yamashita, Tomonori
Iwakura, Kenji
Suzuki, Fumio

ChooseParameter.Other: The polymer underwent resaponification with an aqueous solution of sodium hydroxide
Subsequently, it was dilated with pure water in a cellophane tube (Visking Tube) for 3 weeks with occasional change of water.

Mixing.Description: Aqueous HCl was added dropwise to TEOS while stirring

ChooseParameter.Other: PVA was dropped slowly into silica sol

Heating.Description: The mixture was heated in a water bath

MoldingInfo.Description: The mixture was cast in a polystyrene Petri dish

ChooseParameter.Other: The sol was aged in a sealed dish for 1 week at 40 C.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: The wet gel was dried in air and further in vacuo.
